"I developed an acute appreciation of what problems are that are worth spending your time are, versus problems you just slide into, because you do one thing, you do the next thing, you do graduate work, you end up doing a post doc and before you know it you're working on something and you don't really ever, analyze why am I doing this, and so, believe me, after spending eight years on something that I in retrospect, decided was useless, you start thinking about that a lot"
